id: pm-2muu
title: "Lock contention auto-retry: bounded jittered wait before lock_conflict so parallel agent mutations self-heal"
description: "Parallel mutations on the SAME item still surface lock_conflict too quickly under burst contention: acquireLock (src/core/lock/lock.ts) already retries EEXIST a few times, but it does not wait with a configurable jittered budget before failing. Empirical: 12 parallel `pm update` on one item -> 5 succeed, 7 lock_conflict, even though each lock is held only for milliseconds. Agents firing parallel tool calls (or multiple agent sessions/programmatic spawns) still need hand-rolled retry loops. Fix: bounded jittered wait inside acquireLock before throwing lock_conflict - e.g. settings `locks.wait_ms` (default ~3000, 0 = today's fail-fast) + `PM_LOCK_WAIT_MS` env override + `--lock-wait-ms` flag; poll with jittered backoff (e.g. 25->50->100->200ms) until acquired or budget exhausted. If the wait budget exhausts, include a `retry_after_ms` hint in the structured lock_conflict payload so callers know when to retry. Integrity is already perfect under contention (no corruption, no lock debris, history consistent) - this is purely availability/UX. Note: a single pm-mcp server already serializes via SerialQueue (pm-3puw), so this mainly hits parallel CLI invocations and multiple concurrent MCP/agent sessions on one workspace."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,concurrency,locking
created_at: "2026-07-03T13:25:02.684Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-05T04:18:06.323Z"
assignee: maintainer-agent
author: claude-code-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "acquireLock waits with bounded exponential backoff + jitter up to locks.wait_ms (default 3000ms, PM_LOCK_WAIT_MS override); lock_conflict error carries retry_after_ms recovery hint; parallel-mutation stress shows self-healing without integrity loss; config key locks_wait_ms settable via pm config set and documented; tests cover env override, zero budget fail-fast, and stale-removal cap."
parent: pm-dj98
risk: medium
confidence: high
